isotropy effect entirely. The flowmap texture’s blue channel is ignored."}]}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/basematerial3d\/anisotropyflowmap"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Texture that offsets the tangent map for anisotropy calculations and optionally controls the anisotropy effect (if an alpha channel is present). The flowmap texture is expected to be a derivative map, with the red channel representing distortion on the X axis and green channel representing distortion on the Y axis. Values below 0.5 will result in negative distortion, whereas values above 0.5 will result in positive distortion."}],"references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/BaseMaterial3D":{"kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"BaseMaterial3D"}],"type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Abstract base class for defining the 3D rendering properties of meshes."}],"title":"BaseMaterial3D","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"BaseMaterial3D","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/basematerial3d","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/BaseMaterial3D"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot":{"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot","title":"SwiftGodot","role":"collection","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Framework to write Godot Game Extensions using the Swift Programming Language."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/Texture2D":{"fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Texture2D","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"Texture2D","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/texture2d","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Texture2D","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"Texture for 2D and 3D.","type":"text"}],